This paper deals with modal logic and its decidability, which falls under the category of mathematical logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses practical applications of modal logic, which could be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study of satisfiability and undecidability also has connections to computational complexity (cs.CC) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Finally, the paper discusses first-order definable classes of frames, which is related to programming languages and semantics (cs.PL).
